0Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20asked%20whether%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EMarker%20or%20the%20Cheetah%20Conservation%20Fund%20are%20still%20involved%20with%20Project%20Cheetah%20in%20any%20capacity%2C%20and%20whether%20Marker%20was%20consulted%20when%20some%20of%20the%20cheetahs%20were%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2F4th-cheetah-released-wild-kuno-national-park-tourists-glimpse-9078047%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ereleased%20into%20the%20wild%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20this%20year%20despite%20months%20of%20captivity%20after%20they%20were%20restricted%20to%20enclosures%20for%20health%20check%20ups%20following%20a%20series%20of%20deaths%20last%20year%2C%20Marker%20gave%20no%20direct%20answer%3B%20instead%2C%20she%20said%20that%20it%20was%20an%20%E2%80%9CIndia%20project%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20spent%20nearly%20a%20year%20on%20the%20ground%20teaching%20about%20cheetah%20and%20the%20reintroduction.%20We%20hope%20that%20our%20work%20with%20them%20in%20training%20will%20pay%20off%20for%20the%20cheetahs%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20wrote%20in%20an%20email%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2F27223624%2FUntitled-design-74.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2F27223624%2FUntitled-design-74.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2F27223624%2FUntitled-design-74-300x140.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2F27223624%2FUntitled-design-74-1024x478.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-645937%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ESasha%2C%20a%20female%20cheetah%2C%20at%20Kuno%20National%20Park.%20Photo%3A%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20State%20Forest%20Department.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAdrian%20Tordiffe%2C%20a%20veterinary%20wildlife%20specialist%20currently%20based%20in%20India%2C%20told%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20the%20last%20direct%20communication%20that%20he%20obtained%20from%20Indian%20authorities%20about%20the%20animals%20was%20on%20July%2018%2C%20and%20that%20he%20has%20not%20received%20any%20information%20since%20then.%20In%20an%20exclusive%20interview%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20he%20added%20that%20he%20was%20gradually%20%E2%80%9Costracised%E2%80%9D%20from%20the%20Project%2C%20possibly%20because%20he%20spoke%20to%20the%20media%20about%20the%20cheetah%20deaths%20that%20had%20occurred%20during%20that%20time.%20He%20did%20not%20receive%20any%20information%20about%20the%20death%20of%20the%20seventh%20adult%20cheetah%20on%20January%2016%20either%2C%20he%20told%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20post-mortem%20results%20are%20still%20awaited%20%E2%80%93%20more%20than%20four%20days%20after%20the%20cheetah%E2%80%99s%20death.%20Last%20year%2C%20Tordiffe%20told%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20the%20wait%20for%20the%20post-mortem%20results%20and%20not%20sharing%20information%20with%20the%20African%20experts%20had%20caused%20a%20delay%20in%20identifying%20the%20cause%20of%20the%20first%20cheetah%20death%20due%20to%20septicaemia%20(officially%20listed%20as%20a%20natural%20death%20due%20to%20%E2%80%9Ctraumatic%20shock%E2%80%9D%20by%20Indian%20authorities).%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFollowing%20this%2C%20two%20more%20cheetahs%20died%20in%20a%20similar%20manner%20and%20these%20deaths%20could%20have%20been%20possibly%20avoided%20had%20the%20experts%20been%20in%20the%20loop%2C%20he%20had%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20has%20been%20no%20formal%20communication%20with%20me%20regarding%20my%20involvement%20in%20the%20project%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20told%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20the%20exclusive%20interview%20dated%20January%2021.%20%E2%80%9CI%20have%20written%20to%20the%20chair%20of%20the%20Project%20Cheetah%20Steering%20Committee%20hoping%20for%20some%20reconciliation.%20He%20did%20not%20even%20acknowledge%20receipt%20of%20my%20letter.%20It%20seemed%20a%20waste%20of%20time%20to%20pursue%20the%20matter%20further.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20main%20problem%20with%20Project%20Cheetah%20is%20the%20%E2%80%9Csecrecy%2C%20political%20rivalry%20and%20the%20egos%20of%20the%20people%20involved%E2%80%9D%2C%20Tordiffe%20told%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fproject-cheetah-deaths-radio-collar-infections%5C%22%3EProject%20Cheetah%3A%20Radio%20Collar%20Infections%20a%20%E2%80%98Cause%20for%20Concern%E2%80%99%2C%20Team%20Expert%20Questions%20Ground%20Support%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EPolitics%20over%20science%3F%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20high%20profile%20nature%20of%20the%20project%20has%20created%20a%20situation%20where%20certain%20people%20stand%20to%20gain%20significant%20political%20points%20with%20those%20in%20power%E2%80%A6This%20was%20always%20going%20to%20be%20a%20challenging%20project%20as%20we%20had%20no%20real%20template%20or%20precedent%20to%20work%20from.%20It%20was%20critical%20that%20accurate%20scientific%20data%20was%20collected%20and%20shared%20in%20an%20open%20and%20transparent%20manner%20with%20all%20involved.%20Unfortunately%20that%20did%20not%20happen.%20The%20flow%20of%20information%20is%20now%20tightly%20controlled%20and%20it%20is%20difficult%20to%20know%20what%20to%20believe%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAccording%20to%20Tordiffe%2C%20the%20biggest%20challenge%20%E2%80%9Cis%20that%20management%20decisions%20there%20seem%20to%20be%20based%20on%20politics%20rather%20than%20science%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CScience%20cannot%20advance%20in%20a%20society%20where%20information%20is%20controlled%20by%20those%20in%20power%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%20%E2%80%9CIf%20scientists%20are%20silenced%2C%20conspiracy%20theories%20are%20allowed%20to%20thrive%20and%20people%20and%20animals%20end%20up%20suffering%20unnecessarily.%20The%20truth%20is%20the%20truth%2C%20even%20if%20it%20is%20difficult%20to%20face%2C%20authorities%20just%20do%20not%20want%20to%20acknowledge%20that%20they%20do%20not%20have%20all%20the%20answers.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBoth%20Tordiffe%20(along%20with%20other%20cheetah%20and%20veterinary%20experts%20Vincent%20van%20der%20Merwe%2C%20Andrew%20Fraser%20and%20Mike%20Toft)%20and%20Marker%20had%20written%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20July%20last%20year%20in%20two%20separate%20letters%20regarding%20similar%20issues%3A%20about%20their%20concerns%20in%20being%20kept%20in%20the%20dark%20about%20the%20management%20of%20Project%20Cheetah%20and%20the%20animals%E2%80%99%20health.%20In%20their%20letters%2C%20they%20noted%20that%20some%20of%20the%20cheetah%20deaths%20%E2%80%9Ccould%20have%20been%20prevented%20by%20better%20monitoring%20of%20the%20animals%20and%20more%20appropriate%E2%80%9D%20and%20timely%20%E2%80%9Cveterinary%20care%E2%80%9D%20if%20the%20experts%20were%20informed%20immediately%20rather%20than%20being%20%E2%80%9Cignored%E2%80%9D%20and%20used%20as%20mere%20%E2%80%9Cwindow-dressing%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EIndian%20Express%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Fhave-serious-concerns-how-cheetah-project-is-managed-we-in-dark-foreign-experts-tell-sc-8872128%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ereported%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20Later%2C%20however%2C%20both%20van%20der%20Merwe%20and%20Fraser%20dissociated%20themselves%20from%20the%20letter.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20has%20written%20to%20the%20National%20Tiger%20Conservation%20Authority%20(NTCA)%20for%20details%20about%20whether%20experts%20Tordiffe%20and%20Marker%2C%20or%20the%20two%20others%20listed%20on%20the%20same%20panel%20%E2%80%93%20Fraser%20and%20van%20der%20Merwe%20%E2%80%93%20are%20being%20informed%20about%20the%20cheetahs%E2%80%99%20health%20and%20status%2C%20or%20being%20solicited%20for%20information%20regarding%20the%20animals%E2%80%99%20health%20and%20release%20into%20the%20wild%20after%20several%20months%20of%20captivity.%20The%20story%20will%20be%20updated%20when%20they%20respond.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscience.thewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fkuno-project-cheetah-carrying-capacity%2F%5C%22%3EDid%20India%20Get%20Its%20Math%20Wrong%20About%20How%20Many%20Cheetahs%20Can%20Fit%20In%20Kuno%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EWhy%20expert%20inputs%20could%20be%20crucial%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EInitially%2C%20the%20Project%20Cheetah%20Steering%20Committee%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpib.gov.in%2FPressReleaseIframePage.aspx%3FPRID%3D1927441%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520members%2520of%2520the%2520said%2520Committee%2520are%2520as%2520follows%253A%26text%3DRajesh%2520Gopal%252C%2520Secretary%2520General%252C%2520Global%2CInstitute%2520of%2520India%252C%2520Dehradu%253A%2520Member%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Elisted%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20four%20experts%20%E2%80%93%20Marker%2C%20Tordiffe%2C%20Fraser%20and%20van%20der%20Merwe%20%E2%80%93%20to%20be%20consulted%20for%20advice%20%E2%80%9Cas%20and%20when%20required%E2%80%9D%20because%20Indian%20officials%20and%20veterinarians%20on%20the%20ground%20did%20not%20have%20hands-on%20experience%20on%20African%20cheetah%20health%20and%20management.%20The%20Committee%20has%20not%20officially%20announced%20if%20there%20has%20been%20a%20change%20in%20the%20panel.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20%E2%80%9Cbest%E2%80%9D%20if%20at%20least%20one%20of%20these%20experts%20are%20in%20the%20loop%20regarding%20the%20cheetahs%2C%20Chief%20Veterinary%20Officer%20of%20the%20Wildlife%20Trust%20of%20India%2C%20N.V.K.%20Ashraf%2C%20told%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20Ashraf%20had%20told%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Fcheetah-india-conservation-animal-deaths-17061a2256f61e4f2350e7ccde3f735b%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EAP%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20July%20last%20year%20that%20it%20is%20important%20that%20there%20be%20a%20constant%20line%20of%20communication%20with%20people%20in%20Africa%20who%20have%20expertise%20with%20the%20species%20since%20the%20cheetah%20would%20be%20a%20difficult%20species%20to%20relocate%20and%20grow%20into%20a%20viable%20population.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CI%20hope%20that%20they%20are%20in%20contact%20and%20sharing%20information%20%5Bwith%20one%20of%20the%20experts%5D%2C%20at%20least%20once%20in%20a%20while%2C%E2%80%9D%20Ashraf%20said.%C2%A0%20%E2%80%9CThere%20should%20ideally%20never%20be%20a%20disconnect%20%5Bbetween%20the%20Indian%20ground%20teams%20and%20the%20experts%5D%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESo%20far%2C%20four%20cheetahs%20have%20been%20released%20back%20into%20the%20wild%20in%20Kuno%20since%20December%202023%2C%20after%20being%20confined%20to%20enclosures%20since%20July%20that%20year.%20So%20many%20months%20of%20captivity%20is%20bad%20for%20the%20animals%2C%20experts%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.downtoearth.org.in%2Fnews%2Fwildlife-biodiversity%2Fcaptive-for-months-experts-fear-cheetahs-at-kuno-may-face-breeding-issues-93548%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ehave%20claimed%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%3B%20this%20could%20have%20%E2%80%9Cbiological%20and%20behavioural%20impacts%E2%80%9D%2C%20as%20well%20as%20issues%20with%20breeding.%20Is%20this%20a%20concern%3F%20Close%20monitoring%20could%20be%20key%20here%2C%20Marker%20told%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20over%20email.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThey%20do%20need%20to%20be%20carefully%20monitored%20as%20to%20making%20sure%20that%20they%20are%20able%20to%20hunt%20enough%20as%20they%20get%20going%2C%E2%80%9D%20Marker%20said.%20%E2%80%9CThey%20know%20the%20areas%2C%20since%20they%20were%20out%20before%2C%20and%20they%20know%20how%20to%20hunt.%20They%20should%20be%20OK%20%E2%80%93%20if%20they%20are%20monitored%20closely.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAccording%20to%20Tordiffe%2C%20it%20is%20crucial%20that%20the%20cheetahs%20be%20released%20from%20the%20management%20camps%20%E2%80%9Cas%20soon%20as%20possible%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20not%20clear%20why%20this%20has%20not%20been%20done%20yet%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705805033000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F17142504%2FScreenshot-2023-09-17-at-2.24.53-PM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fcheetah-experts-not-in-loop-information-deaths%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Namibian%20and%20South%20African%20cheetah%20experts%20told%20'The%20Wire'%20that%20