cording%20to%20Microsoft%2C%20Midnight%20Blizzard%20first%20accessed%20the%20company's%20systems%20in%20late%20November%20through%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcovid-19-vaccine-covid-vaccine-north-korean-russian-hackers-microsoft-2020-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%26quot%3Bpassword%20spray%26quot%3B%20attack%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20tactic%20where%20a%20malicious%20actor%20uses%20the%20same%20password%20on%20multiple%20accounts.%20But%20it%20was%20only%20last%20week%20that%20Microsoft%20first%20detected%20a%20threat%20to%20its%20systems%2C%20the%20company%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBased%20on%20Microsoft's%20initial%20investigation%2C%20it%20appears%20that%20Midnight%20Blizzard%20targeted%20corporate%20email%20accounts%20to%20find%20information%20about%20itself%20and%20managed%20to%20withdraw%20%26quot%3Bsome%20emails%20and%20attached%20documents.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosofts-history-in-photos-2015-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMicrosoft%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20%26quot%3Bthe%20attack%20was%20not%20the%20result%20of%20a%20vulnerability%20in%20Microsoft%20products%20or%20services%26quot%3B%20and%20added%20that%20%26quot%3Bthere%20is%20no%20evidence%20that%20the%20threat%20actor%20had%20any%20access%20to%20customer%20environments%2C%20production%20systems%2C%20source%20code%2C%20or%20AI%20systems.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%2C%20however%2C%20had%20a%20similar%20response%20back%20in%202021%20after%20its%20systems%20were%20impacted%20by%20the%20SolarWinds%20attack.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-solarwinds-cyberattacks-transparency-fireeye-cybersecurity-hackers-2021-2%3Fr%3Dkc-sub%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EMicrosoft%20said%20its%20software%20and%20tools%20hadn't%20been%20used%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%26quot%3Bin%20any%20way%20for%20this%20attack.%26quot%