C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EDallas-based%20baby%20apparel%20brand%20Kyte%20Baby%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20been%20under%20fire%20this%20week%20for%20taking%20a%20hard%20line%20on%20remote%20work.%20The%20company%20allegedly%20fired%20its%20studio%20coordinator%20Marissa%20Hughes%20after%20she%20requested%20to%20work%20remotely%20to%20care%20for%20her%20newborn%20baby.%20The%20decision%20sparked%20backlash%20on%20social%20media%2C%20angry%20customers%20began%20boycotting%20the%20brand%2C%20and%20the%20company's%20founder%20and%20CEO%20Ying%20Liu%20has%20apologized%20for%20the%20decision%20on%20TikTok%20%E2%80%94%20twice.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20was%20insensitive%2C%20selfish%2C%20and%20had%20only%20been%20focused%20on%20the%20fact%20that%20her%20job%20had%20always%20been%20done%20on%20site%2C%20and%20I%20did%20not%20see%20the%20possibility%20of%20doing%20it%20remotely%2C%26quot%3B%20Liu%20said%20in%20an%20apology%20video%20she%20posted%20on%20TikTok%20on%20Thursday.%20%26quot%3BThinking%20back%2C%20it%20was%20a%20terrible%20mistake.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ERemote%20work%20request%20%E2%80%94%20denied.%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20saga%20began%20back%20in%20December%20when%20Hughes%20and%20her%20husband%20received%20a%20call%20from%20an%20adoption%20agency%20telling%20them%20about%20a%20newborn%20baby%20in%20the%20intensive%20care%20unit%20in%20El%20Paso%2C%20nine%20hours%20away%20from%20their%20Dallas%20home%2C%20Hughes'%20sister%20Kailee%20Moeller%20said%20in%20a%20video%20on%20TikTok.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20agreed%20to%20let%20Hughes%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeet-the-typical-remote-worker-income-profession-age-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ework%20remotely%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20two%20weeks%20to%20take%20care%20of%20her%20new%20baby%2C%20Moeller%20said.%20Hughes'%20role%20at%20Kyte%20Baby%20involved%20taking%20care%20of%20%26quot%3Beverything%20in%20studio%26quot%3B%20from%20the%20models%20to%20the%20wardrobes%20to%20the%20sets%20for%20the%20company's%20photo%20shoots%20and%20marketing%20initiatives%2C%20according%20Moeller.%20Hughes%20had%20also%20been%20working%20at%20Kyte%20for%20under%20a%20year%20which%20meant%20she%20wasn't%20entitled%20to%20benefits%20from%20the%20Family%20and%20Medical%20Leave%20Act%2C%20which%20give%20certain%20new%20parents%20up%20to%2012%20weeks%20of%20job-protected%20leave.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20details%20of%20Hughes'%20discussions%20with%20her%20managers%20aren't%20entirely%20clear%2C%20she%20seemed%20to%20have%20requested%20a%20more%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmaternity-leave-around-the-world-2018-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eextensive%20maternity%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20leave%20and%20questioned%20why%20she%20wasn't%20entitled%20to%20the%20same%20maternity%20benefits%20as%20her%20pregnant%20colleague%2C%20according%20to%20Moeller.%20The%20company%20ultimately%20told%20Hughes%20that%20if%20she%20didn't%20return%20to%20work%20in%20two%20weeks%20she%20would%20essentially%20be%20forfeiting%20her%20job%2C%20Moeller%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHughes%20never%20returned%20to%20work%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.usatoday.com%2Fstory%2Fnews%2Fnation%2F2024%2F01%2F19%2Fkyte-baby-marissa-hughes-materinity-leave%2F72284395007%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eaccording%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20USA%20Today.%20She's%20been%20posting%20updates%20about%20her%20newborn%20on%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gofundme.com%2Ff%2FJudah-Medical-Fund%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGoFundMe%20page%3C%2Fa%3E%20dedicated%20to%20raising%20money%20for%20his%20medical%20costs.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20extra%20time%20spent%20bonding%20and%20collaborating%20with%20his%20medical%20team%20has%20been%20such%20a%20blessing%2C%26quot%3B%20Hughes%20wrote%20on%20the%20GoFundMe%20page%20on%20Friday.%20%26quot%3BIt%20has%20ensured%20he%20is%20getting%20the%20best%20possible%20care%20while%20he%20continues%20to%20fight.%26quot%3B%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EKyte%20Baby%20founder%20says%20%26quot%3Bit%20was%20a%20terrible%20mistake%26quot%3B%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20drama%20has%20sparked%20a%20wave%20of%20backlash%20on%20social%20media.%20Angry%20mothers%20have%20been%20posting%20videos%20on%20TikTok%20throwing%20out%20their%20Kyte%20Baby%20onesies%2C%20calling%20for%20a%20brand%20boycott%2C%20and%20expressing%20their%20support%20for%20Hughes.%20Momfluencers%20and%20baby%20brand%20founders%20%E2%80%94%20including%20some%20of%20Kyte%20Baby's%20biggest%20competitors%20%E2%80%94%20have%20also%20donated%20thousands%20of%20dollars%20to%20Hughes'%20GoFundMe.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELiu%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20has%20walked%20back%20the%20company's%20initial%20stance%20in%20two%20apology%20videos%20she%20posted%20to%20Kyte%20Baby's%20TikTok%20account%20this%20week.%20In%20the%20first%20one%20she%20posted%20on%20Thursday%20%E2%80%94%20which%20has%20garnered%20more%20than%202.5%20million%20views%20%E2%80%94%20she%20said%20she%20wanted%20to%20%26quot%3Bsincerely%20apologize%20to%20Marissa%20for%20how%20her%20parental%20leave%20was%20communicated%20and%20handled.%26quot%3B%20She%20added%20Kyte%20Baby%20prides%20itself%20on%20being%20%26quot%3Ba%20family-oriented%20company%26quot%3B%20that%20%26quot%3Btreats%20biological%20and%20nonbiological%20parents%20equally.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20video%20was%20criticized%20in%20the%20comments%20for%20being%20%26quot%3Bscripted%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Binsincere%26quot%3B%20and%20sounding%20too%20much%20like%20a%20statement%20prepared%20by%20the%20company's%20lawyer.%20So%20Liu%20posted%20a%20second%2C%20more%20candid%20apology%2C%20in%20which%20she%20admitted%20that%20%26quot%3Bthe%20comments%20were%20right%2C%20it%20was%20scripted.%20I%20memorized%20it%2C%20it%20wasn't%20sincere.%26quot%3B%20She%20acknowledged%20that%20it%20was%20her%20decision%20to%20deny%20Hughes'%20request%2C%20and%20that%20she%20didn't%20%26quot%3Baccommodate%20Marissa%20fully.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELiu%20herself%20is%20a%20mother%20of%20five%20who%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fkytebaby.com%2Fpages%2Four-story%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elaunched%20Kyte%20Baby%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20struggling%20to%20find%20baby%20apparel%20that%20would%20calm%20her%20daughter's%20eczema.%20While%20she%20didn't%20deny%20that%20her%20apology%20was%20motivated%20by%20a%20decision%20to%20%26quot%3Bsave%20face%26quot%3B%20she%20said%20that%20as%20human%20being%2C%20mom%2C%20and%20owner%20of%20a%20baby%20business%20she%20wants%20to%20set%20the%20record%20straight%20on%20the%20%26quot%3Bimpact%20of%20her%20actions.%26quot%3B%20She%20added%20that%20she%20would%20review%20Kyte%20Baby's%20HR%20policy%20and%20noted%20that%20the%20company%20would%20continue%20to%20pay%20Hughes'%20benefits%20and%20keep%20her%20position%20open%20if%20she%20decided%20to%20return.%20The%20video%20has%20racked%20up%20more%20than%205%20million%20views.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKyte%20Baby%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20Business%20Insider's%20request%20for%20a%20comment%2C%20but%20Liu%20told%20USA%20Today%20that%20%26quot%3Bbased%20on%20our%20maternity%20policy%20at%20the%20time%2C%20all%20parents%2C%20whether%20biological%20or%20non-biological%2C%20who%20worked%20for%20the%20company%20for%20at%20least%20six%20months%2C%20received%20two%20weeks%20of%20paid%20maternity%20time.%26quot%3B%20She%20added%2C%20%26quot%3BWe%20continue%20to%20apologize%20to%20both%20Marissa%20and%20our%20Kyte%20Baby%20community%20for%20how%20her%20maternity%20leave%20was%20handled.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkyte-baby-ceo-apologizes-after-denying-employees-remote-work-request-2024-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3